name: Sunset Sail
description:
There is no better place in Seattle to view the sunset than from the deck of our boat, sipping your favorite beverage while watching the sun go down!

On sunset cruises, Seattles sky often turns from a bright, sunny blue, to orange and violet, laced with red. Sailing back into the harbor, the entire waterfront is bathed in a warm, golden light and waterfront windows are ablaze with reflections of the sun.

As the sun sets and dusk settles in, the skyline of downtown Seattle lighting starts to twinkle, outlining the city and the space needle.

itemListElement.name: San Juan Island Sailing Yacht Charter

name: San Juan Island Sailing Yacht Charter
description:
Fly in on a sea plane from Kenmore Air. The flight from Seattle to Friday Harbor only takes 45 minutes and transforms you into a beautiful sunny Northwest Island Oasis that are known as the beautiful San Juan Islands. Here the captain will meet you the Dock to pick up your bags as your San Juan Sailing adventure around the island begins! 

Call for more details and to speak with one of our associates about the sailing itinerary!

itemListElement.name: 2 Hour Lake Union Hot Tub Cruise

name: 2 Hour Lake Union Hot Tub Cruise
description: You’ll arrive at our boat office where we have 2 warm and dry changing rooms for you to get changed. We have storage available for your dry clothes and personal belongings in our locked dry box while you are out on the boat. Then you and your friends (up to 6 people total) will climb into the 100+ degree hot tub and after listening to our brief safety instruction will take off and drive our hot tub boat around Lake Union!

review.name: A perfect way to spend the afternoon/evening
review.reviewBody: I was interested in trying this out last year when   I was on the lake. The lady that helped us was super friendly and informative. The boat was really easy to run. It was perfect having a warm hot tub to soak in after a cool swim. There was a place to store ice for drinks and snacks. The scenery was beautiful with the Seattle skyline and the space needle in the background.

review.name: Super fun experience - best way to enjoy Lake Union
review.reviewBody: So fun!  What a great idea to combine a hot tub and boat.  This company really executed it well - the boat maneuvers well and holds up to the waves/wake in South Lake Union.  Being out in the water in South Lake Union is so nice - the views are incredible, particularly during sunset/at night.  But being out in the water in SLU in a hot tub boat? Next level.  The staff here are also so great, particularly Liam.  They went way out of their way to make our experience special - thank you!  Highly recommend this place!

review.name: DO NOT MISS OUT ON THIS GREAT EXPERIENCE
review.reviewBody: The costumer service was INCREDIBLE and the boat is so fun!!! A great atmosphere to hang out and have a cool experience. Would recommend it to anyone.

review.name: Best plan in Seattle
review.reviewBody:
This is probably the best experience I’ve had in Seattle. 
I was here with my husband last Saturday evening and we decided to go on a boat. It was awesome. The views of downtown from the boat are beautiful. The family who owns this business are very attentive and make sure you feel safe and comfortable at all times. I would recommend to anyone who wants to have a good experience in the city. We’ll do it again for sure. It’s perfect for couples, friends, and families with children.

review.name: Unique and Fun Adventure in Seattle
review.reviewBody:
We did the two hour Lake Union Hot Tub Cruise for my partner’s birthday, with three other friends. Let me tell you...it was SO MUCH FUN! The boats are wood fire heated, so there’s a bonus campfire smell. Cruise right by Gasworks park and cute houseboats in a hot tub. Too cool.

The owner was really friendly and helpful. We were provided with a Bluetooth speaker, and waterproof holders for our phones. The changing room at the dock is very small, but there is a space to lock your belongings.

Highly recommend! I’ll be doing this again!

review.name: Best way to see Seattle
review.reviewBody:
My first time on Lake Union couldn't have been better! Our hot tub boat was simple to drive/use and had everything we needed, from waterproof phone cases, to a bluetooth speaker, to space for beers and snacks. There was a safe spot to stash our stuff on shore while we were out and a heater on in the changing room which was appreciated since it was a chilly night – it made the towels toasty when we returned. 

Our time on the boat was so chill and fun; we only saw a few other boats out and the skyline looked spectacular. I'm recommending this to everyone I know. it's such a unique, fun way to experience Seattle in a new way. Already planning to return in a few weeks!

review.name: Hot Tub Boat
review.reviewBody: Wow. Where to start. End of this story is that this was an awesome adventure!!! It started with the ease of booking on line. Then easy directions and instructions to what to expect and what to do. Once we parked we called and Rex answered right away and waved at us so we knew were to go. Rex was amazing and went over all they do to get ready for us. Our boat was ready!!!! They had cool dressing room and bam we were ready for our boat. Rex has the phone covers as advertised and a Bluetooth speaker. Once in the boat some very easy to understand directions and then off we went. Rex helps guide you out so it’s soooo simple. We spent 3 hours cruising the lake. This was money well spent and I would suggest that you do this. Thank you so much Rex.

review.name: Best Seattle Experience! A wonderful winter evening soak!
review.reviewBody: What a wonderful winter activity!  The water was toasty warm, the boat was easy to drive, and the scenery spectacular.  Thank you Rex and Lake Union Hot Tub for such a unique opportunity. I recommend this experience for anyone looking for something different, out of the ordinary, weather just a couple of friends or the whole family!

review.name: Could not have been better!
review.reviewBody: Wow!  Consistent with the other reviews, our experience was absolutely wonderful.  What is better than getting in a boat full of water, on the water, and also on fire?!  Ha ha... The hot tub was spotless, the water was hot and stayed hot, while the smell of the fire made you feel like you were in a mountain cabin.  Now, add the novelty of sitting in a hot tub in Lake Union with the occasional sea plane landing, or taking off and you have the perfect conditions.  The owner was so incredibly accommodating, provided waterproof bags for phones and gear and also safe storage in the small building associated with the business.  The hot tub had two areas to place MANY beverages if desired.  We all made at least one polar plunge into Lake Union, which was SOOOO cold, but getting back into the hot tub was then a treat.  I'm not one who can usually tolerate a hot tub for long, but this was fantastic.  Highly, highly recommend...especially in winter conditions.

review.name: Sunset Cruise with the Family
review.reviewBody: This is certainly going to be a new family tradition! The entire process was smooth sailing. The owner was super helpful and kind. Changing rooms are in the sweetest, coziest boathouse the owner built with his father in law, located amongst the most incredible of city views. The tub was easy to use and heat to desired temp. The smell of the wood burning fire put the whole experience over the top! Water proof phone cases, a Bluetooth speaker for music, water and towels were all provided! Come rain or shine, this is experience is worth every penny. One of the best things you can do in Seattle as a local or tourist.

itemListElement.name: Cooking Class & Market Tour in Pike Place (Fall Schedule)

name: Cooking Class & Market Tour in Pike Place (Fall Schedule)
description:
Experience Pike Place Market through the eyes of a chef! This cooking class will introduce you to the Market community and give you the opportunity to create a hearty multi-course meal with your chef. We then sit down to indulge in our gourmet dishes. Eat Seattle uses a hybrid demonstration/hands-on format to give the maximum value of teachings and allow those that would like to participate to do so. 

After class, you'll be treated to a brief tour through Pike Place to learn its history and meet our vendor partners.

This cooking class includes a four-course meal with snacks, a starter, main and dessert course as well as wine. We believe in eating real food, full of color and flavor. Quality ingredients are important to us and all of our food is fresh and locally sourced from Pike Place Market wherever possible. We design an experience that is decadent, informative and fun.

itemListElement.name: Tea and True Crime : Ed Gein

name: Tea and True Crime : Ed Gein
description:
What better way to spend a Sunday afternoon relaxing with a cup of tea and a tale or two of murder?

Join horror and true crime buff Kim Douthit at Spooked in Seattle, drink tea and talk some of history’s most notorious true crime.

Edward Theodore Gein, also known as the Butcher of Plainfield or the Plainfield Ghoul, was an American murderer and body snatcher. His crimes, committed around his hometown of Plainfield, Wisconsin, gathered widespread notoriety after authorities discovered Gein had exhumed corpses from local graveyards and fashioned trophies and keepsakes from their bones and skin. 

Due to graphic subject matter, including crime scene photos, no one under the age of 16 is recommended.

name: How to Murder Tour
description: The Pacific Northwest has been home to more than its fair share of the nation’s more notorious killers. This 90-minute Seattle Murder History Tour covers some of Seattle’s most notorious homicide cases. View crime scene photos and hear how some of the perpetrators may have gotten away with murder. Your stroll through the historical streets of Pioneer Square will offer chills, as you learn just how corrupt the city of Seattle was.

name: Pioneer Square Ghost Tour
description:
This 90 Minute walking tour takes you through Seattle's oldest neighborhood, with locations including the Pioneer Square Hotel, the Smith Tower, and Merchant’s Cafe and Saloon, Seattle’s oldest restaurant.

You will hear real stories of the ghosts that continue to haunt the area, topped off by venturing into a portion of Seattle’s famous “underground”, with nothing but a flashlight !

review.name: Fun Evening
review.reviewBody: We were looking for an evening activity and came across this tour.  We really enjoyed it. Kim was a really good storyteller and handled the unexpected very well.  It was a fine way to spend an evening out walking and learning about the neighborhood we were staying in.

review.name: Fun tour!
review.reviewBody: Anita was our guide on this fun tour.  Ghost stories and history is a great way to experience the pioneer square area.

review.name: Fun Experience
review.reviewBody: Great walking tour and stories ranging from the founding of Seattle to the early 2000's. Fun experience and way to explore the history of old Seattle for out of town tourists or locals.

review.name: Interesting stories
review.reviewBody:
We took the tour in September, it was as described. There were about 10 other guests on the tour clearly inebriated.  I feel like the guide delt with the unruly guests well, maintaining professionalism. 
There were some good stories, some good evps.  Interesting museum, but the guide had a photo on the wall of a well known haunted location in Iowa.
He misquoted the name of the town Villisca, calling it something else.  Which made us wonder.

review.name: Just OK, tour guide talked way too fast
review.reviewBody:
Took the tour August 28, after being in town for three games between the Yankees and Mariners.
My biggest issue was with the tour guide. Nice young man but he talked way too fast. 
So fast, he would occasionally stutter or trip over his own words making him hard to understand.
Don't know if he was in a hurry to get it over, as we were the last tour of the night, or he had consumed too much Seattle coffee.
Anyway, the tour started at 7 p.m. Most of the ghost tours I have been on, take place near or after dark, kind of takes the "scary" part out of it with it being full daylight.
He mentioned the hotel I was staying in as being haunted, " Room No. 209 Best Western Plus Pioneer Square" and said there was talk about it on the internet although the hotel denies it.
I could find nothing online that talked about room 209 of that building being haunted. (I was in room 217).
Anyway, it just wasn't the best ghost tour I have been part of.
What was interesting, I had a lenghty conversation with the guide about a paranormal experience I  have had  after it was over and he was not nearly as rushed in his speech.
Maybe he gets nervous in front of crowds.
I also thought we'd get to see more of the underground, but the only part we visited was within their own building.

review.name: I'm a believer!
review.reviewBody: Some pretty strong evidence, very interesting and informative.  Lots of stairs, so missing my exercise classes is no problem.

review.name: This wasn't what we expected
review.reviewBody: The ghost tour wasn't what we thought it would be.  We went on this tour in November and unfortunately it was freezing that night and raining and since it is a walking tour it is all outside. They take you around to different buildings where there have ghost either have been or are still living there, but you don't actually get to go in the buildings. We ended up leaving the tour to get hot chocolate lol. My daughter did get an interesting reading from the Tarot card reader that was there that night at the place you meet for the tour though, so that was really fun.  It might be better on a warmer evening and you are just wanting to hear the history.  We were with 21 year olds who wanted to be in the buildings and hoped to see ghosts.

itemListElement.name: Sea & Sky Day Trip to Victoria, BC

name: Sea & Sky Day Trip to Victoria, BC
description:
Soak in the natural wonders of the Pacific Northwest and travel between downtown Seattle and vibrant Victoria, BC with two of the region’s most popular forms of transportation: ferry and seaplane. Soar through the skies in a 45-minute Kenmore Air flight and soak in fabulous aerial views as you travel from Seattle to Victoria. Spend the day exploring the sights and tastes of the vibrant Victoria, before a relaxing return by ferry to Seattle. 

Daily Schedule: 
Morning - depart Seattle from the Kenmore Air Terminal located at 950 Westlake Ave N, Seattle (departure times vary based on day of week and time of year) 
After a 45 min flight, arrive to Victoria's Inner Harbour
Spend the day exploring Vibrant Victoria 
Evening - Depart Victoria for Seattle at the Victoria Clipper terminal located at Belleville Street Victoria, BC (departure times vary based on day of week and time of year)

name: Escape the Room Activity
description: Quest Factor offers premium live-action escape rooms with state-of-the-art puzzles, compelling story lines and movie like ambiance in the rooms.

review.name: Not very good.  Would go to different escape room.
review.reviewBody: We did Jurassic Island. Aesthetics were great, but puzzles were not very good.  The flow is extremely linear so only one puzzle can be completed at a time - this means only 1 or 2 people are participating. Other escape rooms allow concurrent puzzle solving, so everyone is involved.  The puzzles also required trial & error rather than problem solving to translate... Guessing shouldn't be a requirement.  I've done 10 other escape rooms around Seattle and would recommend any of those over this location.

name: Seattle Scenic Panoramic Tour
description: Uncover the origin of Seattle's "Emerald City" nickname on this city tour! Marvel at the glistening Puget Sound, expansive green forests, and local mountains from stunning viewpoints. Wander through diverse neighborhoods like Ballard and Queen Anne, each offering unique cultural and architectural experiences. It's a fantastic journey to immerse yourself in the beauty of the Pacific Northwest!

review.name: Hop on hop off no show!
review.reviewBody: We purchased our tickets at the ticket booth near pier 54. We expected there would be buses every 15 - 30 minutes. After waiting for over an hour we went back to the place of pur have and asked for a refund, which was steadfastly refused and we were told to contact the company. Being a Saturday no one answered the phone. So we never got to use the service that we paid for.

review.name: Don't expect to get on and off and visit more than 2 attractions
review.reviewBody: The hop on hop off route was verbally noted on the bus to take 1 1/2 hours, which was virtually impossible. We intended to do the route starting at 10 am. to get a general view of Seattle and then pick a stop to have lunch. It took 2 1/2 hours to complete the route and another 1/2 hour to get to Pike Place. Had lunch, went to pickup stop, and waited an hour for a bus, which was overcrowded, gave up on seeing other attactions and took another 1 1/2 to return to our starting point. Better off to pick places you want to go and Uber around town.

review.name: Terrible, no correspondence at all amd money owed!
review.reviewBody:
I booked in Oct 14th this yesr not knowing that the last day fornthe yesr was the 13th October! 

Thankfully i have receipts of what i paid and when i paid for which is in April 2025! The website says you can cancel anytime up to 24-48hrs for a full refund and ive been trying since oct to get my refund back a good 6 months before partaking in a tour! 

I have trued numerous times to contact them via e-mail to no avail even though they still send me e mails not regarding my enquires but to sell more products to purchase! 

I have sent receipts, account numbers all to no avail! They have my wise account as thats how i puchased the tickets! 

I really do hope they see this review and fully reinstate my funds as they are part of my 50th celebration funds!

review.name: Fantastic!
review.reviewBody: Our driver was funny. Made our trip memorable. I enjoyed it very much. Highly recommend this company. It went to the landmarks

review.name: Bad deal
review.reviewBody: Very disappointing. We usually always use hop on hop off busses when we travel. This one was horrible. Only two buses operated all day for the whole route. Had to wait long time. Also there were many e scooters blocking the aisle which made if almost impossible to get on and off the bus. We ended up walking too many of the sites. Not worth the money we paid.

review.name: Great tour guide
review.reviewBody: We did the 3 hour guided tour.  Our guide was very interesting and knew a LOT of history about the city.  My husband and I both thoroughly enjoyed it!

review.name: Wonderful experience, Very Informative!
review.reviewBody: Our Scenic Seattle Panoramic Tour was  informative and wonderful. Olivia is an Awesome tour guide and ensured that we had the best experience ever. I absolutely encourage everyone visiting Seattle to try this tour, you will not be disappointed!

review.name: Amazing combo tour!
review.reviewBody:
We had a full day to spend in Seattle after disembarking our cruise and catching our flight home. We selected the 3-hour tour and hop on/off combo and were really happy with the experience. The hop on/off is about an 80 minute loop that stops just about anywhere you'd want to visit.   We grabbed coffee at Pike Place then caught the bus there. (Stat focused and be prepared to duck to avoid tree branches if you sit up top!)
We then took the 2:00 tour and it was better than we'd expected!  Our guide was knowledgeable and some of the stops were unexpected and really fun.   So much to see beyond what the hop on/off bus visits.

review.name: Seattle, A Wonderful Destination
review.reviewBody: Seattle is a wonderful destination. We made the best of it in the three days we spent in there.  We played in the snow at Mt. Rainier. We visited the Aquarium (it’s small and doesn’t compare to the Monterey Bay Aquarium) so if that’s what you’re expecting, it’ll be disappointing. We went to a Mariner’s Baseball game. It was very exciting, they won in a 9th inning grand slam walk off. Visited Kerry Park, the Space Needle, Chihuly Garden & Glass, Fremont Troll, rode the Seattle Center Monorail, visited Pike’s Place and the yucky gum wall.

review.name: Poor
review.reviewBody: Not very enjoyable!  Waited for about 1 hour for a pick up.  Long waits.  Next time use Uber for your destination!  Very disappointed

name: The Museum of Flight Tour
description: Experience a sightseeing tour which tells the story of how Seattle came to be one of the most successful cities in the world. Explore The Museum of Flight at Boeing Field with its new Apollo 11 Mission exhibit. Museum admission is included with your purchase.

itemListElement.name: Gilbert's Cheese Experience at Cedar & Spokes Coffee & Bar

name: Gilbert's Cheese Experience at Cedar & Spokes Coffee & Bar
description:
We combine our extensive knowledge to provide food education and tasting experiences that are both fun and informative. We draw upon Brian's experience as an American Cheese Society Certified Cheese Professional and Head Cheesemonger at Beecher's Handmade Cheese in Seattle, and Holly's background as a food and beverage journalist and blogger. 

We host cheese-pairing pop-ups with Seattle-area food and beverage producers, providing a delicious sampling of locally procured products and insider access to craft producers. We'll teach you how food and beverages are made, and how to do a tasting. You'll also meet the producers and hear the stories behind the local businesses we love! 

These are fun, interactive experiences where you can mix and mingle with us, other guests and local food and beverage producers. You'll sample amazing foods and drinks, learn some new things and most importantly, have a great time!

itemListElement.name: Bitter Is Sweet: The Amaro + Cheese Experience

name: Bitter Is Sweet: The Amaro + Cheese Experience
description:
We offer our own rich knowledge of cheese, food and beverage, plus insider access to local products and producers at Seattle-area culinary destinations. 

Brian Gilbert is a 20-year veteran of the food and beverage industry with a lifetime of passion behind him. He is a Certified Cheese Professional (CCP), and also serves as Head Cheesemonger at Beecher’s Cheese in Seattle's Pike Place Market. Brian has spent nearly a decade making, aging, selling and procuring cheese while educating the community. His mission is to convey food's vital role in local ecosystems and how that knowledge makes us better consumers and citizens.

Holly Regan is a professional writer, editor and marketer with subject-matter expertise in food, beverage and travel. She is an aspiring vegetarian chef, food blogger and content business owner. With a background in anthropology; her mission is to explore and connect the world’s cultures, people and places as expressed through their art, customs and cuisine.

itemListElement.name: Haunted Seattle Booze and Boos Ghost Walking Tour

name: Haunted Seattle Booze and Boos Ghost Walking Tour
description:
This combination ghost tour and pub crawl that will take you on a walking tour to explore the fascinating history of Seattle and hear some of its most famous and creepy haunted stories. 

A costumed guide will lead tour goers on a 2-2.5 hour journey, offering glimpses into the past and revealing the stories of long-dead phantoms and specters who still call Seattle home. You'll visit several different bars and have time to enjoy a delicious libation (at own expense) as the guide tells you about all the spooky happenings and great history of this amazing town!
*Tour route and drink stops are subject to availability. 
*All guests must be 21+ with Valid ID. Alcohol is not included.

review.name: Ask for tour guide Katherine!
review.reviewBody: Highly recommend! My best friend and I had a blast. The guide, Katherine , was an amazing storyteller. Not only did you get some haunted stories but some history of Seattle that was very interesting as well. Three locations and three drinks and the time flew by. Definitely do this while visiting Seattle!

review.name: Katherine the Great!
review.reviewBody: Katherine was the best guide! So informative, funny and passionate about the task at hand. Highly recommend to anyone wanting to learn a bit more about the market and haunted history of the city.

review.name: Fun spooky evening
review.reviewBody: It was a very fun evening, our tour guide Emily was very attentive to our needs our needs on the trip, and facilitate a fun evening of spookiness without pushing the scary envelope too far!

review.name: Katherine was great! Ghosts abound!
review.reviewBody: Our guide Katherine was fantastic! We learned so much about Seattle and enjoyed great drinks in the process. I can’t wait to revisit some of these places and search for ghosts!

review.name: Our leader was amazing! Lots of fun and full of interesting information. Everyone was included and she welcomed everyone
review.reviewBody: Very fun. Took into account everyone. Made sure everyone was enjoying themselves. Pace was good and frequent stops so no one lagged behind.

review.name: Great for locals and tourists alike
review.reviewBody:
Katherine was a great host and story teller! As a local, it's always a treat to learn more about my home city and get a different perspective. The Seattle Underground is also a great tour and though some stories aligned (good thing!), this tour was uniquely its own. 

I'm told each guide has their own flair, but if your get Katherine, you're in for a great time!

review.name: The highlight of our trip!
review.reviewBody: We had an incredible time on this tour! Our guide Emily was super charismatic and very  knowledgeable about local history and of course had amazing stories on top of it all!  You get to see so many parts of downtown you might not of known existed and the stories/history you learn about will make you appreciate Seattle more than you already should! I would highly recommend this tour to anyone!!

review.name: Nisha is the best!
review.reviewBody: Nisha did an incredible job. She was so friendly, knowledgeable, and energetic. She made the night so much fun, and her stories were enthralling. I would definitely recommend this tour to anyone who’s interested in good drinks and a good time.

review.name: Amazing Tour and Tour Guide!!
review.reviewBody: Absolutely loved the tour and Nisha was an amazing tour guide! They were funny, very knowledgeable, and kept the energy throughout. The stories were great, the drinks were delicious, and it was an overall great time. Would highly recommend this tour to explore Seattle.

review.name: Katherine is amazing!
review.reviewBody: Katherine is so amazing! She made the tour fun and emmersive! She is passionate about what she does and knows how to draw you in! We highly recommend this tour with her! 💗

itemListElement.name: Whiskey + Cheese Experience With Woodinville Whiskey

name: Whiskey + Cheese Experience With Woodinville Whiskey
description:
Brian and Holly are Gilbert's Cheese Experience. We host cheese-pairing pop-ups with Seattle-area food and beverage producers, providing a delicious sampling of locally procured products and insider access to craft producers. 

We're excited to bring you this special collaboration with Woodinville Whiskey Co.: an award-winning producer of handcrafted, small-batch spirits located in Woodinville, Washington. Sample their delicious portfolio of bourbon, rye and port-finished bourbon whiskey, and experience the magic that happens when it's combined with local artisan cheese selections. These are beautiful flavor combinations that you may not even have thought to try — and the bold, spicy flavors are perfect for fall!

It all takes place at Cedar & Spokes Coffee & Bar, a cafe located in Seattle's iconic Pike Place Market.

itemListElement.name: Savor a unique SUNSET hike with us!

name: Savor a unique SUNSET hike with us!
description:
This hike strikes a balance of being accessible to most with a base fitness level and challenging and short enough to never get boring. We initiate all of our experiences with a mindfulness practice to leave behind the hustle of daily life and invite you to be fully present in Nature. After enjoying a delicious picnic on the ledge, we'll descend as twilight turns to darkness. No worries though, this is a well maintained trail and we've got you covered with headlamps and flashlights. 

We will meet in Seattle to ride together to the Rattlesnake Ledge trailhead. On the way we will pause to admire the region's largest and most impressive waterfalls, Snoqualmie Falls - a sacred place according to beliefs of the native Snoqualmie people.

name: Seattle Scandals History Tour
description: It is the only tour in Seattle that has more than 10 stops (and therefore more than 10 stories) in Pioneer Square. All the other tour companies focus on one small detail, and they will go to only one, maybe two locations at the most. But, we go to at least 8 locations on each one of our tours, and guests will hear at least 8 different stories of Seattle's fascinating history.

review.name: THE BEST tour I ever had!
review.reviewBody: Without a doubt, THE BEST, most interesting tour I have ever been on! Bobby was SO informed, had such great stories, and a grasp of Seattle through the years!  If you can only take one tour... and love to hear the stories behind the city.... this is the one tour you want!

name: Ghost Tour in Seattle
description: It is unique because we get to go into several haunted locations. Also, unlike other tours, we have more than 10 stops on the tour. Most other companies go to only 2 or 3 locations.

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: Tour guide was extremely knowledgeable. This was more of a tour where you take it at the pace of the group, as opposed to a strict schedule, which is nice.

itemListElement.name: Leavenworth, Mount Rainier National Park 2-Day Tour from Seattle

name: Leavenworth, Mount Rainier National Park 2-Day Tour from Seattle
description:
Learn about all the history of Leavenworth, a famously well-known German Town!
Take a glance at its unique Bavarian-inspired treasures.
Try an authentic local German pork trotter meal with sausage and dark beer!
Explore the unique combination of snow and volcanic landscapes at Mount Rainier!
Enjoy the natural beauty of Mt. Rainier with its spectacular waterfalls (Christine, Narada, Myrtle), vast lakes and lush green forests.

Room Details
All hotel rooms are based on two Full / Double beds or one King/Queen bed depends on what hotel availiable on the day. The maximum occupancy per room is four travelers.

One Room Selection 
If you are a party of more than four guests or desire to have separate rooms, please provide a separate booking.

Avoid traveling in a different bus?
If you have more than one booking, please provide all confirmation numbers once your bookings are complete.

itemListElement.name: City Sightseeing Seattle Hop-On Hop-Off Bus Tour + Harbour Cruise

name: City Sightseeing Seattle Hop-On Hop-Off Bus Tour + Harbour Cruise
description: Experience the very best that Seattle has to offer with a City Sightseeing hop-on hop-off bus tour! You can explore at your own pace with either a 24 or 48-hour ticket. Discover key landmarks such as Space Needle, Pioneer & Occidental Square, Chinatown, Seattle Central Library, Capitol Hill, Pike Place Market and much more! This tour even features a live guide in English so you can learn all about the history of Seattle as you cruise around. This ticket also includes a Self-Guided Walking Tour so you can explore the Pioneer Square historic district and learn about Seattle's early days. Additionally, you can take a 1-hour Harbour Cruise to take in the breathtaking views of Seattle from the water!

review.name: City Sightseeing in Seattle equals Frustration in Seattle
review.reviewBody: We are big fans of hop on hop off tours but were terribly disappointed with our experience in Seattle.  We bought a combo ticket on line for a bus tour and harbor cruise.  We followed the directions to report to stop 1 to schedule our harbor cruise and found no one who knew what to do.  The attendant at the Kiosk was of no help.  The attendants at Stop 1 tried to call someone, but that was of no help.  We went to the Argosy boat tour provider and got no help there.  They referred us to the City Sightseeing Kiosk at Pier 55, which was closed.  In the end we had to buy our own tickets for the boat ride so we double paid.  The experience and frustration ruined what should have been a nice relaxing day.  Very sad.  Even sadder, I found an online customer link and emailed in my concerns.  I have not received a response and it has been five days.

itemListElement.name: Homemade Italian Pasta With Classpop! in Seattle

name: Homemade Italian Pasta With Classpop! in Seattle
description: What sets this Italian pasta-making class apart is the immersive experience it offers. Led by Chef Seamus, this class is not just about cooking; it's a journey into Italian culture and cuisine. The regional insights and the intimate atmosphere make it a truly unique and memorable culinary adventure. Plus, you will savor the delicious Italian Pomodoro sauce, adding that extra touch of authenticity.

itemListElement.name: The Museum of Flight Entrance Ticket

name: The Museum of Flight Entrance Ticket
description: Get ready to travel through air and space at the Museum of Flight with this admission ticket. Explore over 160 air and spacecrafts from the Boeing 787 Dreamliner to the Supersonic Concord at the largest independent, non-profit air and space museum in the world! There are 175 aircraft and spacecraft and tens of thousands of artifacts and rare photographs. Tour Air Force One, 747,and more in the Aviation Pavilion and then head beyond to the Space Gallery to see a Space Shuttle Trainer.

review.name: Experiencia inolvidable
review.reviewBody: Una experiencia increible para los amantes de la aviacion. Tiene mucho para mejorar, pero aun asi es increible. Aviones de la primera y segunda guerra mundial, de la guerra de corea, aviones comerciales, motores y partes de las misiones apollo y de los sovieticos.

review.name: Outstanding flight aerospace museum!
review.reviewBody: Wow! This facility tops the Smithsonian Air and Space museum.  5 planes open for walkthrough. Loved being inside the Boeing 747. Air Force One. Concorde. Space shuttle training plane. WWI and WWII exhibits best we’ve ever seen. Featured decorated Pilots from all over the world - Germany and Russia. Female pilot exhibits great. Flight simulators to play with. Cafe busy and food just right. Volunteers and staff knowledgeable and helpful. Allow 3-4 hours to experience it all.

review.name: ME ENCANTO TODO
review.reviewBody: HERMOSO! EDUCATIVO! ASOMBROSO!! GENIAL!!  Todos las areas muy bien distribuidas y equipadas. Diversos juegos y experiencias para niños, jóvenes y adultos. Salas llenas de INCREIBLE HISTORIA! 🤩👍👏👏👏👏

review.name: Couple trip
review.reviewBody: This was absolutely fantastic, we ended up spending around 4 hours walking round and looking at  and in the exhibits. The staff are really helpful and knowledgeable. Price was great and ample parking a real must do

review.name: Flying High
review.reviewBody: All types of airplanes to see and walk through.  Lots of history of flying.  Some walking required to go to all the areas but well worth it.

review.name: Boeing museum 7.5/10.0
review.reviewBody:
Very fun overall. Shows the entire history of three Boeing company. It would be more accurate to call this the Boeing museum. But that didn't take away from the impressive nature of the museum. 
7.5/10.0

review.name: Super Flugzeug-Ausstellung
review.reviewBody:
Sehr eindrucksvolle Ausstellung, v.a. die Originalflugzeuge sind sehenswert (zivil wie militärisch). Natürlich nur Boieng-Flugzeuge (bzw der fusionieren Firmen), Ausnamhe ist eine Concorde, die auch inner besichtigt werden kann.
Interessant sind auch die Erklärungen bezüglich der Entwicklung der Luftfahrt (Postflüge etc.)
Nicht billig, aber es lohnt sich.

review.name: Tolles Museum
review.reviewBody:
Tolles Museum,  viele Ausstellungsstücke 
Sehr interessant,  besonders das unkomplizierte Ansehen der Flugzeuge , vorallem auch innen

review.name: Must see!!
review.reviewBody: Was absolutely fantastic!!! We went on free first thursday!! And spent over 2 hrs going through the 3 buildings. There was multiple floors and exhibits in each. Lots of interactive things. And multiple planes to fo on!

review.name: Superb - absolutely worth a visit.
review.reviewBody:
Brilliant place - so glad we stopped here.
There are so many exhibits, you could spend an entire day and still not take in everything. 
The space exhibit has masses of brilliant items, loads of Apollo information, including part of the Lunar Module, a lunar rover and even, behind glass, a small piece of moon rock.
Planes include the US Blackbird, an Air Force One, and best of all, a British Airways Concorde. 
So many things to see, laid out very well - thoroughly recommend visiting this museum.

itemListElement.name: Preserving Pike Place: Market Community Tour

name: Preserving Pike Place: Market Community Tour
description:
Get a truly unique perspective of Seattle’s iconic Pike Place Market on this walking tour that gives back to the marketplace community! Your local guide will lead you through the maze of the market, exploring its evolution through the historic buildings and stories of vendors past and present.

Along the way, we may catch a show of the famous flying fish, pass by the oldest existing Starbucks, and make our way to one of the city’s most unusual attractions, the Gum Wall. 

While you’ll get to experience the most visited sites of the market, you’ll also receive a deep appreciation of the Pike Place Market Foundation and the array of services they provide to create a strong community that keeps the market going and benefits those in need.

Best yet, your ticket price already includes a donation to the Foundation, you’ll be giving back to the community yourself!

Your guide will point out great places to eat, drink, and explore based on your interests for the rest of your stay in Seattle!

itemListElement.name: 2 Hours Walking Tour with Breakfast & Coffee at Pike Place Market

name: 2 Hours Walking Tour with Breakfast & Coffee at Pike Place Market
description: Your guide is a retired chef with an obsession for local history. Chef Carolyn will guide you through this vast 9 acre market and introduce you to iconic coffeehouses and local bakeries. You will learn the history of coffee and food in Seattle and the market, while sampling amazing breakfast bites and coffees.

name: Wine Thru the Market
description: Whether you're a seasoned wine aficionado or a curious novice, this 2-hour walking tour promises an unforgettable journey of discovery bringing together the best of Seattle's Pike Place Market and its exceptional wine offerings in a perfect blend of clture, taste and enjoyment. As you wander throughout the back alleys of the market you will have the opportunity to taste dandelion wine, grapefruit Prosecco wine, tasting from a local winery and enjoy a selection from a local tasting room.

itemListElement.name: Sip and savor award winning Yakima Valley wines.

name: Sip and savor award winning Yakima Valley wines.
description:
Discover the flavors and personalities of Central Washington wines. We guide you through our rich growing region and offer one-of-a-kind experiences with many wine varieties, wineries, and vineyards. 

From intimate to widely-known wine producers, our tours are designed to provide an opportunity to see, feel, and experience from ground to glass.

Yakima Valley stretches from the City of Yakima to Benton City. Within the Yakima Valley we tour different regions:

Yakima Area - Friday
Zillah Area - Monday, Wednesday, Saturday
Prosser, Sunnyside, Benton City Areas - Sunday

review.name: Excellent wine touring and tasting experience
review.reviewBody: I had little time to try and figure out wineries I wanted to sample so I put my faith in Little Hopper for my tasting experience. Wendy selected excellent wineries for the tour, two of them taking fresh approaches to winemaking which I appreciated! She provides a fun experience and sincerely cares about the winemakers and their craft, imparting that to her clientele. The snacks in the van were perfect for the venue. I will definitely return to Yakima for more tastings, both wine and beer, and definitely recommend Little Hopper for you tasting experience.

review.name: Great tour - Highly Recommended
review.reviewBody: What a great tour!  Wendy is so pleasant to be with, and really knows the local wine scene. She brought us to amazing wineries, shared her local knowledge, and put us in the capable hands of the winery staff. I had so much fun, that I signed up for the brewery tour the next day! I highly recommend!

review.name: Wine tasting, the way to go.
review.reviewBody: Visited three wineries, all were beautiful and great wine.  It was enjoyable, memorable and beautiful.  Thanks to Juliette for sharing her home.

review.name: You’ll have fun on a Little Hopper Tour!
review.reviewBody: A great way to spend a Saturday!  Fun to meet new people, share conversation and laughs. The wineries were all unique and interesting. Also enjoyed the accompanying staff from Little Hopper. Nice people.

review.name: Best Wine and Beer Tour Guides in Yakima
review.reviewBody: Our experience with Little Hopper was absolutely fantastic!  If you are in Yakima and looking for a beer or wine tour, do not look any further because no one is better than Little Hoppers.  We met Wendy (the owner) and Julieann (our driver) during our trip to Yakima.  Wendy worked with us so we could have an outstanding wine tour.  She emailed us with tour details and included several recommendations for places to eat and things to do in Yakima.  Her recommendations were spot on!  She went out of her way to ensure our trip to Yakima was an enjoyable experience.  We truly enjoyed and appreciated the time we spent with her on our ride to/from the Hop’s Festival.  Julieann was more than just our driver during our wine tour.  She provided excellent information about the wines,  wineries, and the Yakima area.  More importantly, she was an absolute joy to hang out with.  We had fun conversations on the bus and when she checked in on us at the wineries.  All the wineries that were selected were excellent.  Wendy and Julieann are two of the nicest people you will ever meet and will ensure your Little Hopper experience is outstanding!  They are the Ambassadors of Yakima!  You will be missing out if you don’t book your tour with Little Hoppers.

address.streetAddress: 334 NE Northgate Way 334 NE Northgate Way

name: Bainbridge Island Pickleball Experience
description:
Looking for a fun and active summer day trip idea? We’ve got you! Our Bainbridge Island, WA pickleball tours take groups to the birthplace of pickleball during the summer months.

Jen & Madeleine, your friendly and knowledgeable tour guides (and certified pickleball coaches), provide transportation for your group throughout the 5-hour tour. You’ll visit points of interest and historic pickleball locations, enjoy scenic ferry rides, and get a chance to play with your group. We’ll provide hand-crafted, gourmet boxed lunches, and lots of fun pickleball facts!

Our tours are great for people visiting from out of town or those just looking for a unique and enjoyable summer outing with friends and family. Kids are welcome too! No pets, please.

Minimum group size is 4 people and we can take up to 8. Depending on group sizes, we may merge two smaller groups.

review.name: Pickleball Fans - this is for you!
review.reviewBody:
Such a great experience! My wife and I are fairly recent pickleball enthusiasts, and live in the Seattle area. We took my father who has been playing for over 10 years as a birthday gift. Its a great way to learn the origins & history of the sport.  Its also just a beautiful area.
You get a glimpse of the homes where the sport was born (its amazing to see how many folks have private courts in that area!). Playing at the Founders court was a real highlight! Madeline and Jen are knowledgable - plugged into the sport and the region, and fun! Also - Great lunch provided!

review.name: An over the top pickleball experience!
review.reviewBody:
I so enjoyed this special pickleball field trip! Our guides thought of everything that made the trip go smoothly. From our seamless pick-up to the perfect timing of fun stops we made.

The day was magical as we ferried across the water and saw the beautiful mountains and Seattle skyline. We played pickleball trivia which was a great way to provide more pickleball history.

The Founder's local pickleball courts were so nice to play on and I loved the ambiance of all of the people there to play and enjoy each other's company. It was just the right amount of time, at each stop, to fit everything in. 

The yummy lunch stop was awesome as was time to browse through the local farm and garden store, which was much more, with all kinds of fun items to peruse. The island museum and pickleball gift shop all added to this amazing experience.

I would define the day as FUN, SUSPENSFUL AND EXCITING!  There was not a moment of time I wasn't enjoying this field trip! 

Thank you for this over the top pickleball experience!

review.name: Amazing!!!!!!
review.reviewBody: The PPA Tour had so much fun during this tour, the pros that went cannot stop talking about it to this day! We are so thankful for both Jen and Madeleine for taking us on the tour! If you're a pickleball fanatic you NEED to go on this tour and see where our favorite sport originated!

review.name: Bainbridge Tour and Play
review.reviewBody: Best day ever for PB enthusiast!  Jen and Madeline are so knowledgeable and gave a great informative, entertaining and fun tour.  We visited and learned the origins of PB, went to great local food/shopping, and we played PB at the most beautiful courts ever!  I would highly recommend especially if you are visiting Seattle.  Beautiful island and ferry ride.

itemListElement.name: Yakima Valley Hop Farm & Beer Sensory Tour

name: Yakima Valley Hop Farm & Beer Sensory Tour
description:
Yakima Valley is known as the hop capital of the world. Take part in a hop and beer experience and visit family hop farms that have been in the Yakima Valley for generations. Learn about the history of hops and the French-Canadian families who have been farming for over 120 years.

Little Hopper Tours and Rooted Yakima Valley present the Yakima Valley's first Hop Farm and Sensory Experience.

Visit family hop farms, tour a hop processing and production facility, and walk among the hop vines. Through hop sensory activities, you will learn about different hop varieties and understand hops' role in brewing great craft beers. Just like brewers from around the world, you will rub hops in the hop selection room and taste beers produced from the farms' hops. 

Fresh with the knowledge and appreciation of hops, Little Hopper will shuttle you to one of Yakima Valley's award-winning breweries for a look beyond the taproom.

Visit Bale Breaker Brewing, Single Hill Brewing, or Varietal Beer Co.

itemListElement.name: Where the Hops Grow! Yakima Brewery Tour

name: Where the Hops Grow! Yakima Brewery Tour
description: Discover the flavors and personalities of Central Washington craft breweries. We guide you through our rich hop-growing region and visit Yakima Valley's award-winning taprooms and breweries. From small-batch to widely-known, distributed craft brews, our tours are designed to provide an opportunity to see, feel, and experience breweries in the Hop Capital of the U.S. CHEERS TO THAT!

review.name: West side Band
review.reviewBody: Wendy is Top Notch and this was our 3rd trip on The Little Hopper in the last two years.  Once again, it was an awesome trip and we will be be going back again for sure.  Shout out to all the business's that we stopped at too. All were very accommodating.

review.name: Amazing views and beer
review.reviewBody: Wendy was super helpful and flexible with my request. We visited three breweries, the views were amazing, and the beer was so good. The views were amazing at Cowiche Creek Brewing Co!

review.name: Repeat Hoppers.
review.reviewBody: Another great trip on the Little Hopper!!  Dana did an excellent job in getting us around and making us all feel welcome.  Never a rush, allowing us plenty of time to relax at each stop.  Wendy does a fantastic job communicating ahead of time to make sure all of the details are covered.  We will be back again for sure!!!

review.name: Turnkey MTB
review.reviewBody:
Fantastic day trip.  Small group ( 3 riders and guide).  Our guide, Ken, was super friendly and a strong, knowledgeable rider
Beautiful trails and easy pick up and drop off from hotel.
Lunch was excellent - tasty!
